ation has been linked to a greater number of superfund toxic waste sites than has honeywell honeywell ranks th in a list of us corporations most responsible for air pollution releasing more than  million kg  million pounds of toxins per year into the air in  honeywell agreed to pay  in civil penalties and to perform  worth of reparations for environmental violations involving failure to prevent or repair leaks of hazardous organic pollutants into the air failure to repair or report refrigeration equipment containing chlorofluorocarbons inadequate reporting of benzene ammonia nitrogen oxide dichlorodifluoromethane sulfuric acid sulfur dioxide and caprolactam emissions in  a federal judge in newark new jersey ordered the company to perform an estimated  million environmental remediation of chromium waste citing a substantial risk of imminent damage to public health and safety and imminent and severe damage to the environment in the same year honeywell paid  million to avoid a federal trial regarding its responsibility for trichloroethylene contamination in lisle illinois in  the state of new york announced that it would require honeywell to complete an estimated  million cleanup of more than  kg  lbs of mercury and other toxic waste dumped into onondaga lake in syracuse ny as of november  honeywell has completed dredging the lake and established three water treatment plants and the chemicals cleanup site has removed  tons of mercury in  the state of new jersey sued honeywell occidental petroleum and ppg to compel cleanup of more than  sites contaminated with chromium a metal linked to lung cancer ulcers and dermatitis in  the state of arizona made a settlement with honeywell to pay a  million fine and contribute  million to a local airquality cleanup project after allegations of breaking waterquality and hazardouswaste laws on hundreds of occasions between the years of  and  in  honeywell announced that its decision to stop manufacturing mercury switches had resulted in reductions of more than  kg  kg and  kg respectively of mercury lead and chromic acid usage the largest reduction represents  of mercury use in the united states the epa acknowledged honeywells leadership in reducing mercury use through a  national partnership for environmental priorities npep achievement award for discontinuing the manufacturing of mercury switches criticismedit harvey cox holding a honeywell fragmentation bomb  on march   the wsj reported that honeywell was one of sixty companies that shielded annual profits from us taxes in december  the nonpartisan liberal organization public campaign criticized honeywell international for spending  million on lobbying and not paying any taxes during – instead getting  million in tax rebates despite making a profit of  billion laying off  workers since  and increasing executive pay by  to  million in  for its top  executives honeywell has also been criticized in the past for its manufacture of deadly and maiming weapons such as cluster bombs see alsoedit companies portal electronics for medicine garrett airesearch honeywell aerospace honeywell turbo technologies honeywell  novar plc trend controls sperry corporation top  us federal contractors cybra the mircom group of companies referencesedit  a b c d e f honeywell international inc  annual report form k filing date feb   honeywellcom retrieved march     krauskopf lewis  july  honeywell to merge turbocharger business into aerospace unit reuters retrieved  october    honeywell  annual report honeywell annual reports honeywell international  march  p  retrieved  october    a b c d hon k  pdf investorhoneywellcom retrieved  august    fortune  ranking  fortunecom retrieved august     edgar online sec filings fy  yahoobrandedgaronlinecom retrieved september     ed crooks and james politi financial times honeywell chief warns on debt gridlock jul   retrieved jul    david m cote forbes retrieved jul    tom bergeron njbiz honeywell opens truly awesome building in mo